  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Do I need a Facebook Business page for my demolition company?",
    answer: "We set up the Messenger integration during your onboarding — if you do not have a Business page yet, our team creates one with you on the call in about ten minutes. Demolition companies posting dramatic project footage — high-reach sequences, controlled collapses, and cleared site reveals — typically already have an active page, so yours may be ready to connect immediately."
  },
  {
    question: "What demolition enquiries come through Messenger?",
    answer: "A combination of property investors, small developers, and homeowners. Property investors message about redundant commercial buildings they want cleared for redevelopment. Small developers enquire about site clearance costs for residential projects. Homeowners ask about garage, outhouse, and conservatory demolition. All are pre-engaged leads — they have already reviewed your project content and decided you can handle their work."
  },
  {
    question: "How fast does the AI reply to demolition messages?",
    answer: "The response arrives within seconds. Facebook's active status indicator shows your demolition company is engaging immediately. Developers comparing demolition firms for a tender — all of whom post impressive takedown footage — typically award the tender to the company that responds first with relevant technical questions about the project scope."
  },
  {
    question: "What does Messenger cost for demolition companies?",
    answer: `This add-on is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month. Demolition contracts span from £1,500 domestic garage clearances to £500,000 structural projects. One developer tender, secured through a rapid Messenger response while competing firms' messages sat overnight, pays for the channel cost for the foreseeable future.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I continue the Messenger conversation personally?",
    answer: "Drop your own response into any thread and the AI steps aside permanently. It detects your reply and relinquishes control. Most demolition contractors let the AI capture the initial project scope — building type, frame construction, floor area, programme timeline, and asbestos status — then take over to discuss access logistics, plant deployment, and tender pricing."
  },
  {
    question: "How is Messenger data from demolition queries protected?",
    answer: "All Messenger conversations, building images, site addresses, structural details, programme timelines, and contact information are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Data goes exclusively to you. No project details are disclosed to competing demolition firms, shared with adjacent site occupants, or sold to any third party."
